<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-06T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="725" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d725">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1177</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SAG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-06T11:00:00+01:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                            </date> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8:30 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Referring to my cable of November 4, 5 p.m., the Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs informed me Norwegian Government has sent a protest to the
                            British Government against closing of the North Sea. Denmark and Sweden
                            will do same. Norway depends on the United States for large amount of
                            supplies. The Minister for Foreign Affairs expressed a hope that they
                            will have the support of the United States and the United States
                            Government will protest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SAG1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>